---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// SEO: Schema estructurado para que Google entienda las entidades
const groupsSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SportsEvent",
  "name": "World Cup 2026 Group Stage Draw",
  "description": "Complete breakdown of the 12 groups for the expanded 48-team FIFA World Cup in North America.",
  "startDate": "2026-06-11"
};

// VENTAJA TÉCNICA: Simulamos la base de datos de los 12 grupos. 
// Cuando se haga el sorteo oficial, solo actualizás este array o lo conectás a tu API.
const fetchGroups = async () => {
  return [
    { name: "Group A", teams: ["Mexico", "A2", "A3", "A4"], venueRegion: "West / Central" },
    { name: "Group B", teams: ["Canada", "B2", "B3", "B4"], venueRegion: "West" },
    { name: "Group C", teams: ["USA", "C2", "C3", "C4"], venueRegion: "West" },
    { name: "Group D", teams: ["Argentina", "D2", "D3", "D4"], venueRegion: "Central / East" },
    { name: "Group E", teams: ["France", "E2", "E3", "E4"], venueRegion: "East" },
    { name: "Group F", teams: ["England", "F2", "F3", "F4"], venueRegion: "Central" },
    { name: "Group G", teams: ["Spain", "G2", "G3", "G4"], venueRegion: "West" },
    { name: "Group H", teams: ["Brazil", "H2", "H3", "H4"], venueRegion: "East" },
    { name: "Group I", teams: ["Portugal", "I2", "I3", "I4"], venueRegion: "Central" },
    { name: "Group J", teams: ["Germany", "J2", "J3", "J4"], venueRegion: "West" },
    { name: "Group K", teams: ["Italy", "K2", "K3", "K4"], venueRegion: "East" },
    { name: "Group L", teams: ["Netherlands", "L2", "L3", "L4"], venueRegion: "Central" }
  ];
};

const groups = await fetchGroups();
---

<Layout 
  title="FIFA World Cup 2026 Groups: The 48-Team Draw & Seedings" 
  description="Explore the new 12-group format. See where the seeded nations are placed and how the 48-team World Cup 2026 groups are structured."
  schema={groupsSchema}
>
  <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-6 text-blue-900 tracking-tight">The 12 Groups: A New Era of Chaos</h1>
  
  <article class="prose lg:prose-lg max-w-none mb-12 text-gray-700">
    <p>Let’s clear up the confusion right now. FIFA originally tossed around the idea of 16 groups of three teams. Thankfully, they scrapped it. The official <strong>FIFA World Cup 2026 groups</strong> will consist of 12 groups of four teams (Groups A through L). The traditional math is back, but the stakes are completely different.</p>
    
    <p>With 48 nations in the mix, just being a top-two team isn't the only way out. The eight best third-placed teams will also punch their tickets to the knockout rounds. This changes the entire dynamic of the final matchday in the group stage. A late goal in a seemingly boring Group J match could suddenly eliminate a massive team in Group C.</p>
    
    <p>Below is the live structure of the draw. The host nations (USA, Mexico, Canada) automatically headline their respective groups, while top-tier seeds like defending champion Argentina fill the rest of the Pot 1 slots.</p>
  </article>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
    {groups.map((group) => (
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 overflow-hidden group">
        
        <div class="bg-blue-900 text-white px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold m-0">{group.name}</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold bg-blue-800 px-2 py-1 rounded text-blue-200" title="Expected playing region">
            {group.venueRegion}
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          {group.teams.map((team, index) => (
            <li class="px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
              <span class="text-gray-400 font-bold text-sm w-4">{index + 1}</span>
              <span class={`font-medium ${index === 0 ? 'text-blue-900 font-bold' : 'text-gray-600'}`}>
                {team}
              </span>
              {index === 0 && (
                <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-bold text-green-600 bg-green-50 px-2 py-1 rounded">Seed</span>
              )}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-xl">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">How the Draw Works</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-0">
      Teams are divided into four pots based on the FIFA Men's World Ranking. The exception is the host nations, who are automatically placed in Pot 1 and assigned to specific groups to ensure they play on home soil during the opening stage.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>